ActOther Than Statutory Authority
SubjectConfirmation of Masset Indian Reserve No. 1
PrecisOrder confirming that 8.48 hectares (20.95 acres) of land were set apart on July 29, 1938 for the use and benefit of the Old Massett Village Council as part of MASSET INDIAN RESERVE NO. 1, located in the Skeena-Queen Charlotte Regional District approximately 1.5 kilometres from the Village of Masset, British Columbia.
